ale to broker shop network with W-2 base $85K-$150K plus per-loan basis-point compensation 10-25 bps plus territory volume bonuses. Florida mortgage industry features 48-state multi-state licensing pathway substantial for independent brokers with multi-state NMLS reciprocity plus state-by-state surety bond plus E&O plus Florida no-state-income-tax driving substantial top-producer concentration plus Florida purchase plus refinance plus Non-QM market substantial plus Latin American business hub plus corporate relocation purchase market. Income economics feature pipeline plus close cycle dynamics: typical 30-45 day close cycle from application to funding faster than RE broker but with substantial pre-application origination work plus per-loan commission economics typical 50-200 basis points of loan amount depending on company plus role plus LPC vs BPC structure plus Dodd-Frank Regulation Z 12 CFR 1026.36 LO compensation rules prohibiting compensation tied to loan terms with mandatory 3-loan rolling-average compliance methodology plus anti-steering provisions plus LPC lender-paid compensation vs BPC borrower-paid compensation structural choice. Mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income for W-2 base plus commission plus bonus with 24-month averaging plus continuity narrative documenting active pipeline plus closed loan history plus NMLS license continuity. B3-3.2-01 self-employed for 1099 LO operating Schedule C / single-member PLLC plus Form 1084 cash-flow analysis with add-backs NMLS license plus CE costs plus E&O insurance plus business use of home plus technology plus marketing plus auto plus professional development. B3-3.4-02 partnership / S-corp for independent principal broker shop owner with branch P&L override plus K-1 distributions plus Form 1084 entity-level analysis at shop entity level. Multi-source synthesis combining W-2 base plus commission plus bonus plus 1099 plus K-1 plus spouse W-2. Conventional Jumbo for HNW top-producer MLOs pl